# Deploy: service naming and ports

Use when editing compose files or config in the deploy repo.

## Service naming (required)

- **Backend:** `<project>-backend` (e.g. `newswebsite-backend`, `myapp-backend`). One per app.
- **Frontend:** `<project>-frontend` (e.g. `newswebsite-frontend`, `myapp-frontend`). One per app.
- **Extra backends** (workers, resolvers, etc.): `<project>-backend-<role>` (e.g. `tiktoksearch-backend-urlresolver`). Same project prefix, port 8080.
- **Database** (if needed): `<project>-db` (e.g. `newswebsite-db`).
- Use **lowercase** and **hyphens** only. Project name = directory name under `deploy/`.
- Service names must be **unique** across all compose files.
- Add `container_name: <service-name>` so `docker ps` shows clean names (e.g. `newswebsite-backend` not `newswebsite-newswebsite-backend-1`).

## Port convention (required)

- **All backends:** listen on **8080** inside the container.
- **All frontends:** listen on **80** inside the container.
- Do **not** publish these ports to the host; only Caddy publishes 80/443. Services are reached via `proxy-net` by service name.
